    "Suppose n k is an increasing sequence of indices, such that statement (i) n holds for every n = n k. For each k ∈ N, there exists some i k ∈ {1,..., N -1}, such that (5.13) holds for every x ∈ Q i k with n = n k. Thus, there is at least one i 0 ∈ {1,..., N -1} and an increasing sequence of indices k l ∈ N, such that for everyx ∈ Q i 0 and every l ∈ N, (5.13) holds with n = n k l. By passing to the limit on the left hand side using (5.12), we obtain that also (i) holds with i = i 0.",
